note: Title supplied by cataloger; other title from bookplate first flyleaf recto.
Bookplate with title, author, and number 58 pasted onto front flyleaf recto.

msContents.summary: A commentary on the book about the astrolabe by Naṣīr al-Dīn al-Ṭūsī; some diagrams and tables; the final leaf is a later replacement.

persName.#text: Birjandī, ʻAbd al-ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad ibn Ḥusayn, active 16th century
برجندي، عبد العلي بن محمد بن حسين،
Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad,  1201-1274
طوسى، نصير الدين محمد بن محمد،

supportDesc.extent: 127 foliated leaves, 4 unfoliated leaves : 185 x 125 (130 x 80) mm, bound to 187 x 130 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Rubrications in red; diagrams and tables in red and black.

binding.p: Bound in reddish brown leather over pasteboard with blind-tooled double frame; bright blue pastedowns.

origin.p: The copy is undated, but a note places it in Iṣfahān in the month of Rajab 1270 A.H. (f. 1r). It was likely copied in the 18th or 19th century.

provenance: Formerly owned by Abū al-Ḥasan Dallāl (?) (note dated 1270 A.H., f. 1r).
Gift of Sam Schaefler (library bookplate inside front cover).
